    • Constructor Detail

      • MixedDataKey

        public MixedDataKey​(java.util.UUID id,
                    java.lang.String desc,
                    java.lang.Class<T> type)
        Only the combination of id+desc+type must be unique to uniquely reference any value.
        Parameters:
        id - Unique id common to a *set* of keys -- all keys belonging to an isolated sub-system using the IMixedDataDictionary would generally use the same id value. This prevents name (description) clashes between sub-systems sharing a common dictionary.
        desc - A String description/name of the key.
        type - A Class object representing the type of the value that this key references.
